# Software Requirements Specification (SRS)

## 1. Introduction
### 1.1 Purpose
This document outlines the software requirements for a **Product and Inventory Management System** that includes authentication, role-based authorization, a drag-and-drop storefront builder, customer segmentation, marketing tools, and AI bot integration.

### 1.2 Scope
The system will allow admins to manage users, products, and inventory while enabling shop customers to browse and purchase products. Additionally, users can design storefronts, configure themes, manage SEO, and automate marketing campaigns.

### 1.3 Definitions, Acronyms, and Abbreviations
- **Admin**: A user with full control over the system.
- **Vendor**: A user who manages inventory and product listings.
- **Customer**: A shop visitor who can purchase products.
- **SEO**: Search Engine Optimization.
- **AI Bot Agent**: A chatbot integrated into the storefront.

---

## 2. System Features
### 2.1 Authentication and Authorization
- User signup via email and phone number.
- Role-based access control.
- Admin can assign roles and manage users.

### 2.2 Product and Inventory Management
- Admin and assigned roles can manage products.
- Products available with different variants.
- Products tagged with different labels.
- Categorization of products into categories and subcategories.
- Location-based product availability.
- Users can order products from vendors and track orders.

### 2.3 Storefront Builder
- Drag-and-drop builder for landing pages and product pages.
- Theme and style guide configuration.
- SEO management, including meta tags and keyword optimization.
- Users can create multiple landing pages with different paths.
- Custom domain support for user storefronts.
- Automatic subdomain assignment.

### 2.4 Customer Management and Segmentation
- Users can segment customers based on criteria.
- Ability to contact customers via email, SMS, WhatsApp, and other channels.
- Bulk messaging capability.

### 2.5 Marketing and Automation
- Kanban board for marketing planning.
- Copywriting assistance.
- Facebook page and shop integration.
- AI bot agent to assist customers on storefronts.

---

## 3. Non-Functional Requirements
### 3.1 Performance
- System should handle high traffic efficiently.
- Fast response time for storefront interactions.

### 3.2 Security
- Secure authentication mechanisms.
- Role-based access control for different user types.
- Data encryption for sensitive information.

### 3.3 Scalability
- The system should support an increasing number of users and products.
- Cloud-based infrastructure for better scalability.

### 3.4 Usability
- Intuitive UI for storefront builder.
- Mobile responsiveness for storefronts and admin dashboard.

---

## 4. Assumptions and Dependencies
- Internet connectivity is required for full functionality.
- The system will integrate third-party services like SMS, WhatsApp, and Facebook.
- AI chatbot will require an external NLP model integration.

This SRS serves as the foundation for developing a robust and scalable product and inventory management system.

